Body: Love the idea of this project. I must have looked at thousands of ICO projects over the last 18 months. Most of the ICOs I've seen have a slew of competitors. But as far as I can tell, this one seems to have its own niche. It seems to have that "first mover" advantage. It's like a decentralized, tokenized UBER/AIRBNB app for parties. At first, I wondered how the blockchain could benefit such a project, but with verification of party goer and party hoster data, I suppose this project has the same need for the decentraliztion of data as do other social apps like Facebook that are now suffering as a result of their centralization of users' data. What a fun idea for an ICO.

Body: The peer-to-peer service economy is growing. Organizations like Uber and Airbnb are empowering individuals to connect with clients directly from their smartphones. The next clear step in the evolution of this sector is decentralization. Tuurnt.io is ahead of the game by creating a peer-to-peer service app that has no central authority. The Tuurnt token functions as a form of internal capital for the services provided. As the value created by Tuurnt hosts inherently increases the value of the service and therefore the token, one would expect to see more people participating in the Tuurnt 'micro-economy.'  I'm very excited to see how apps like Tuurnt grow over the next decade. We could see a fundamental shift in how we both work and play. But we are also bound to see a lot of flops in this new economy. Let us hope the developers are able create an end product that can stand the test of time.

Author: throwinuptheleaves
Title: [ANN] [AIRDROP] 🔥 TuurnT.io 🔥 - $80000 available - Progress: 2084/8000
Body: I watched the Tuurnt video and am excited about this project.  The web is already being seen as "old" and outdated (and in a jaded view "fake") so competitors like evite are going to be left behind.  Some of the things I like about Tuurnt are the ability to find events in the nearby area spontaneously and the host reviews aspect.  I have some curiosity how Tuurnt will deal with ratings gaming and then there's the question of how does someone who is a new host compete in a field of 5 star established hosted events?  I'm a bit old so appreciate back in my clubbing days that part of a night out of fun was the adventure and risk associated with finding a good club so I think I miss that on behalf of younger people these days that that bit of mystery is removed from the experience.  I hope Tuurnt's ratings ask specific questions about why people do or do not like a place.  Some of my favorite clubs had concrete floors and were dives but had awesome bands and decent drinks and there should be a way to merge the various nuances of what makes a good vibe.  Looking forward to watching and following this project and supporting it.

Author: myminex
Title: [ANN] [AIRDROP] 🔥 TuurnT.io 🔥 - $80000 available - Progress: 2084/8000
Body: Earn Tokens for Hosting & Attending Events Our goal at Tuurnt has always been to create a close-knit community of hosts and partygoers. Now that we have accomplished this goal, we would like to expand our community by introducing the Tuurnt Token (TRT) into the platform.  TRT will empower the Tuurnt ecosystem by incentivizing event creation and attendance. This will be accomplished by awarding tokens to users on a monthly basis.  This award driven business model would not only provide a new revenue stream for party host, but also make the currently burdensome process of storing crypto assets easier by integrating a social wallet into the Tuurnt app.  The social wallet will also easily enable transactions between host, guest and friends, providing seamless transactions on the blockchain  The funny project, You can replace fb in future! Author: coinadon
Title: [ANN] [AIRDROP] 🔥 TuurnT.io 🔥 - $80000 available - Progress: 2084/8000
Body: Earn Tokens for Hosting & Attending Events  Our goal at Tuurnt has always been to create a close-knit community of hosts and partygoers. Now that we have accomplished this goal, we would like to expand our community by introducing the Tuurnt Token (TRT) into the platform.  TRT will empower the Tuurnt ecosystem by incentivizing event creation and attendance. This will be accomplished by awarding tokens to users on a monthly basis.  This award driven business model would not only provide a new revenue stream for party host, but also make the currently burdensome process of storing crypto assets easier by integrating a social wallet into the Tuurnt app.  The social wallet will also easily enable transactions between host, guest and friends, providing seamless transactions on the blockchain.  Reward System  The two primary functions for TRT are to book payed or free events listed on Tuurnt and to send TRT to friends and other Tuurnt users. These two functions create a closed economy for the Tuurnt ecosystem and will ensure stability. In addition to the primary functions, TRT will be awarded to Tuurnt users based on our level system. The Tuurnt level system consists of two sub-categories, one for events hosts and the other for partygoers.
